    "actor_description": "It’s still there—heavy—but I stop pushing against it for a breath. The tightness in my chest gives a little, like a knot finally deciding to loosen. I feel sad, unmistakably, but the sadness isn’t a fight right now; it’s just real. A small exhale slips out of me and, for once, it doesn’t feel like surrender—it feels like settling.",
    "description_text": "{actor} goes quiet in a different way—shoulders easing, breath lengthening, eyes softening as if the struggle inside has paused. The sadness remains visible, but there’s a faint release in their posture, a steadiness that reads like letting the loss be true without wrestling it.",
